                <h4></h4>

    
              <p>And/or one of:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-272" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 272 Earth's Changing Surface (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26562" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Geography (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Geography              : Introduction to the study of landforms as products of geomorphic and geologic systems acting at and near the Earth's surface. The process geomorphology approach will be used to demonstrate how landforms of different geomorphic settings represent a dynamic balance between forces acting in the environment and the physical properties of materials present.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Wayne H Pollard (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>3 hours</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
