                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/anth-339" class="program-course-title">
              ANTH 339 Ecological Anthropology (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-17762" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Anthropology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Anthropology              : Intensive study of theories and cases in ecological anthropology. Theories are examined and tested through comparative case-study analysis. Cultural constructions of "nature" and "environment" are compared and analyzed. Systems of resource management and conflicts over the use of resources are studied in depth.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

